29/06/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The Supreme National Defence Council has presented its performance report for 2004, saying activities were aimed at implementing security strategy objectives and tasks related to Euro-Atlantic integration. According to the document, parts of which were cited by the Rompres news agency Wednesday (29 June), the Council focused on fighting corruption, organised crime, trafficking, and international terrorism. The report will now be reviewed by parliament.
In other news, imports sharply outpaced exports in the first five months of 2005, prompting the government to consider measures to reduce the trade deficit. According to figures released Tuesday, imports rose by 22.4 per cent year-on-year, while exports increased by 19.4 per cent. (Rompres - 29/06/05; AP - 28/06/05)
